{{Quote|There are dark places in the galaxy, where few tread. Ancient centers of learning, of knowledge, but I did not walk alone.|Kreia|<ref name="TSL">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>}}
The '''Trayus Core''' was the innermost sanctum of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Trayus Academy]] on [[Malachor V]].

==Description==
Located at center of the [[Trayus Academy]] on [[Malachor V]], the core was a claw-like altar&mdash;suspended above a massive geyser of [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] energy&mdash;stabilized by three bridges that connected to the rest of the Trayus Academy.<ref name="TSL" />

==History==
The Trayus Core, like the rest of the Trayus Academy, survived the [[Battle of Malachor V]]. During the [[Sith Civil War]], it was within the Trayus Core that [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]] [[Darth Nihilus]] and [[Darth Sion]] defeated and [[Exile (punishment)/Legends|exiled]] their [[Sith Master/Legends|master]], [[Kreia|Darth Traya]], seeking to take her power and rule the [[Sith Triumvirate]] themselves. However, after the [[Battle of Telos IV|deaths of Nihilus]] and Sion, the Jedi Exile [[Meetra Surik]] found Traya meditating in the Trayus Core, where she proceded to [[Battle of Malachor|kill her]].<ref name="TSL" />

The Trayus Core emitted such a high degree of [[The Force/Legends|Force]]-based energies that it allowed Traya to center herself there, so much so that she was able to predict the fate of Surik's companions, except for that of [[Bao-Dur]], [[HK-47]] and [[T3-M4]], even going so far as to reveal the [[Declaration of a New Order|eventual fate]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] itself. When the [[Mass Shadow Generator/Legends|Mass Shadow Generator]] was reactivated, the Trayus Core collapsed into itself as Malachor V and the rest of the Academy were destroyed around it, dispersing the dark side energies contained within.<ref name="TSL" />

